JOHANNESBURG (miningweekly.com) &ndash; A range of growth opportunities, including the potential acquisition of the Youga gold mine and Balogo deposit, in Burkina Faso, is being considered by dual-listed miner Avesoro Resources to further its strategy to become a premier midtier African gold producer. The two assets in Burkina Faso are currently owned by the company&#39;s majority shareholder Avesoro Holdings. Independent technical reports are being prepared by CSA Global to provide a guide as to their valuation in any potential future transaction.